  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening  Accountability within the Zambia Response to Food Insecurity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. A capacity assessment of  disaster management mechanisms  and agencies. This will help provide information on planning of response interventions which might include cash transfers, recovery input support and the rehabilitation of water points and .  2.  Assessment of Cross -cutting issues: Conduct an assessment on existing gender, protection, participation and grievance management mechanisms in order to address existing information and response gaps in these areas. This is an opportunity to start identifying and  developing mitigation and recovery interventions. Also to provide evidence to call for urgent early action from government and other actors to prevent the situation from further deteriorating and ensuring that people do not experience further loss of food, livestock and income. 3. Training of agencies (WVI, Oxfam, and Government), district and sub -district community structures in Disaster Risk Management (DRM), and cross cutting issues such as Gender and Protection.</narrative>
  </description>
